AGI - The President of the Council, Giorgia Meloni, will be in London: in the morning for a bilateral meeting with the Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Keir Starmer, scheduled at 12 Italians in Downing Street, during which will address in particular the war in Ukraine, the issue of irregular migrations and cooperation in the defense sector, and in the afternoon, starting from 15 Italians, to participate in the summit on European common defence and the security of Ukraine, convened by the same Starmer.
&nbsp;
The summit, which will be held a few hours after the hard confrontation in the Oval Studio between US President Donald Trump and Ukrainian President, Volodymyr Zelensky, aims to "take Europe's action on Ukraine" and to reiterate "our unwavering collective support to ensure a just and lasting peace and a lasting agreement, which guarantees the future sovereignty and security of Ukraine".
&nbsp;
The leaders of all continental Europe were invited, including France, Germany, Italy, Denmark, the Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Spain, Finland, Sweden, the Czech Republic, Romania, but also Turkey, as well as representatives of NATO (Mark Rutte) and the European Union (Ursula von der Leyen and Antonio Costa) and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky.
&nbsp;
The meeting, which precedes even a few days the Extraordinary European Council which will be dedicated to the same themes, will be based on the talks of Paris, hosted by French President Emmanuel Macron two weeks ago, and will focus on the "strengthening of the position of Ukraine now, including ongoing military support and increased economic pressure on Russia".
&nbsp;
"Every division of the West - Meloni declared yesterday - makes us all weaker and favors those who would like to see the decline of our civilization. Not of its power or its influence, but of the principles which founded it, first of all freedom. A division wouldn't suit anyone. We need an immediate summit between the United States, the European States and allies to speak frankly about how we intend to face today's great challenges, starting from Ukraine, which together we have defended in recent years, and what we will be called to face in the future. It is the proposal that Italy intends to make to its partners in the coming hours".
&nbsp;
This evening the premier had a telephone conversation Trump>, also in sight - informs Palazzo Chigi - of the meeting that will be held tomorrow in the British capital with Zelensky.
&nbsp;
On Wednesday, at the end of a meeting at Palazzo Chigi with Swedish premier Ulf Kristersson, Meloni also stated that "NATO remains, even more after the entry of Sweden and Finland, the cornerstone of our security, but must also have an approach that is as much as possible to 360 degrees".
&nbsp;
"To do so - it has specified - we have to spend more, but also to be able to increase the investments. I think that the choice, announced, of President Ursula von der Leyen to exclude defence expenditure from the Stability Pact is a first step, but to this must follow other solutions."
&nbsp;
Italy, according to some journalistic reconstructions, would be ready to rise to 2.5 percent of the GDP for military spending for NATO, from the current 1,56%. The U.S., moreover, would have communicated to the European allies that from now on the British will have the leadership to protect Ukraine.&nbsp;
